My mother - my mother and father used to read - when we were younger you know, was all round - sitting round the fire and then they would - there was Bibles on the Su
nday night you ken, he would read them. A funeral, I mind - funeral of my uncle Dave, and - us ladies and - his nephews like, we carried him shoulder high to the churchyard that was just - where - where the garage is. Across and into the churchyard. And w
e carried him shoulder high.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3749059 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3502717\charrsid14223522 Who all went to that funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid620671 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3502717\charrsid14223522 Oh - all - all the menfolk, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3749059 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3502717\charrsid14223522 What about your kind of dress?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid620671 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3502717\charrsid14223522 
Oh - well, there was - the dark - real dark clothes. See, was young then and - just dressed in your Sunday best. But - we went into {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Edinburgh{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 like my - to my aunt's. Duncan and I. Like we was twins you see, we'd go down there for a fortnight or a week you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3749059 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3502717\charrsid14223522 
What about going visiting relatives in Lauder, is this something the family always did together, did you go to visit relatives at certain times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid620671 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3502717\charrsid14223522 
Oh no, we just - my grannies - me father's -mother you know in Lauder. Mother's mother you see. Oh yes, visit them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3749059 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3502717\charrsid14223522 Kept in touch with them all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid620671 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3502717\charrsid14223522 Yes. Boys like, oh well you had - we had - the job
s to do in the house before we got away like, with boots - boots to clean for the Sunday all like that and - and then we got away and - and - went - went hounds and hares and - a lot go games then, with the balls and the - and the - aye, the marbles. And 
then the gird - the gird. And then cotton bot and - shillick and the like of them. Hounds and hares.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3749059 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3502717\charrsid14223522 How would you spend the Sunday?
