Oh well you've got - got - about the - what folk in the place like - you have - we had a millwright. You've got all that haven't you - well we - we had - millwright with millwrights. 
We had a cooper. Yes. And then we had - a vet. A doctor. Three - three public houses. Three public houses. And - the - The Eagle Hotel, The Black Bull Hotel and the Commercial Inn, that was the three at our end. Then we had - two drapers shops, in fact th
e
re were - three. Two big drapers shops and one smaller drapers shop. And then a big linen shop. We had - David Baine - Baine - Liddle, John Liddle and - Reed was the licensed grocers. Aye. Oh aye. Doctor - we'd one doctor. And a vet. And then we had as I 
say between seventy and eighty horses at that time. There was maybe eighteen to twenty in the Black Bull - stables. You see, they had the brakes, they went to - they - they nearly only went to Stow.
