Aye, in - in older days, but of course the - the depot is - in Lauder, there was a depot in Lauder.
 Aye. Aye, all the stuff was carted to - and they traced the horse, it was a very steep hill you understand and they trace them up and left the cart and went in and got another you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3749059 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3502717\charrsid14223522 You say they traced them up, what does that mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid620671 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3502717\charrsid14223522 Put a tr
ace horse - two horses, one in the cart you see. And - and one with the chains on. As an extra - in front you see. Pull them the load you see. One - it - it was very - severe winters long ago, so much so that at one - on one occasion, there maybe more tha
n
 one but one special winter they - driver of the - of the bus, we'll call it the bus - had to leave his horse and - for the - for this - for the - drifts and whatnot, and they couldna get him, you know he was lost. And my father - went out with the rest o
f
 them seeking for him. They took a bugle - bugle wi' them and they sounded the bugle, and - then they - they got him. Away at the targets. Now the targets is up the Burn Hill. You know the - you know where the targets are? Well they got him across there. 
So he had - instead of coming down that way you see he had cross there walking. So that like - see what - he was walking on the top of the dykes up younger with the snow really.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3749059 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3502717\charrsid14223522 Was he alive?
