,
 there was like - these runaways. And there was one episode I think it's worth the mentioning. Was an old fellow, Moffat they called him, and he had a pair of horse, went across - he was going for the coals at Sutra, you see they used to take the - the - 
t
he corn and whatnot in from Lauder away into Edinburgh and come back wi' coals, from the - from Tyne - Tynesiders. So they - they - this time he went away with his pair of white horse and - with like one in front and - they had the pair. No, there was two
 
white horse you see and when they were passing Sutra town - you know - you know the horse of his pair - you see, they were - they were again at the back again at the front. So his pair - catched - the porch and broke it down. So they said he had three whi
t
e horses, again at the back and one at the front. So they was - big great commotion but they went on - kept on and - when they were - when they come back you see they were looking for the - the pair of white horses, but they had mixed them up you see. Tur
ned the white horse away another bit - you see, other - other lot and when of course they left the young white horse first of course they came looking for the - the fellow with the apair you see. So he got through with them.
